<sect1 id="tool-fitsviewer">
<title
>Outil d'affichage <acronym
>FITS</acronym
></title>
<indexterm
><primary
>Outils</primary>
<secondary
>Afficheur FITS</secondary>
</indexterm>

<para
>FITS, or Flexible Image Transport System, is the standard format for representing images and data in Astronomy. The &kstars; FITS Viewer is a tool to view those images. It is not designed for editing of FITS Images.</para>

<para
>The FITS Viewer can be automatically invoked for images received from the camera. It can also be invoked directly from the main &kstars; menu. To open a FITS file, select the <menuchoice
><guimenu
>File</guimenu
> <guimenuitem
>Open Image...</guimenuitem
></menuchoice
> menu item, or press <keycombo action="simul"
>&Ctrl;<keycap
>O</keycap
></keycombo
>.</para>

